## PART 2: TP5 - Network Firewall (pfSense) - Website Blocking

### What is Network Firewall?
A **network firewall** (gateway firewall) is:
- Hardware/software that sits between network and internet
- Inspects ALL traffic for the entire network
- Blocks/allows based on rules (IP, port, protocol)
- Examples: pfSense, Cisco ASA, Fortinet FortiGate

### Key Concept: Aliases
**Aliases** are groups of IP addresses or domains
- Instead of creating 1 rule per IP, create 1 rule for an alias
- Simplifies management: change 1 alias instead of 100 rules

```
Without Aliases: 1 rule per website = 100 rules
BlockedWebsites Alias: Contains 100 websites = 1 firewall rule
```

---

## TP5: Blocking Websites with pfSense

### Architecture
```
Internet
    ↓
pfSense Firewall (10.10.1.1)
    ↓
LAN Network (10.10.1.0/24)
    ├─ Machine-1 Admin (10.10.1.11)
    └─ Web Server (10.10.1.16)
```

### Step 1: Access pfSense Web Interface

**Why:** Configure firewall from web dashboard

```
Any machine on LAN:
Browser → https://10.10.1.1
Click Advanced → Proceed to 10.10.1.1 (unsafe)
Username: admin
Password: pfsense
```

### Step 2: Find Website IP Address

**Why:** Firewall rules work with IPs, not domain names

```
Admin Machine-1 Command Prompt:
ping rediff.com
```

**Output Example:**
```
PING rediff.com [84.53.185.208] with 32 bytes of data:
Reply from 84.53.185.208: bytes=32 time=19ms TTL=49
```

**Note:** Some websites have multiple IPs - add all of them

### Step 3: Create Alias for Blocked Websites

**Why:** One alias = one firewall rule instead of many

```
pfSense Dashboard:
Firewall → Aliases → IP tab
Click "Add" button
```

**Configure Alias Properties:**
```
Name: BlockedWebsites
Description: Restrict access to unwanted websites
Type: Host(s)
```

**Add Website Information:**
```
IP or FQDN: www.rediff.com
Description: Site URL

Click "Add Host" button:
IP or FQDN: 84.53.185.208
Description: Site IP address
```

**Save the Alias:**
```
Click "Save" → Click "Apply Changes"
```

### Step 4: Create Firewall Rule

**Why:** Rules tell firewall what to block/allow

```
Firewall → Rules → LAN tab
Click "Add" button (up arrow)
```

**Configure Rule Details:**
```
Action: Block (deny access)
Interface: LAN
Address Family: IPv4
Protocol: TCP/UDP (both web protocols)
```

**Source Section:**
```
Source: any (all computers)
```

**Destination Section:**
```
Destination: Single host or alias
Select: BlockedWebsites (our alias)
Destination Port Range: any (all ports)
```

**Extra Options:**
```
Description: Restrict access to unwanted Websites
```

**Save and Apply:**
```
Click "Save" → Firewall/Rules page appears
Click "Apply Changes"
```

**Status Message:**
```
"The changes have been applied successfully. 
The firewall rules are now reloading in the background."
```

### Test Website Access

**Before Blocking (Step 1):**
```
Web Server Browser:
Type: http://www.rediff.com
Result: Website loads successfully ✓
```

**After Blocking (Step 4):**
```
Web Server Browser:
Type: http://www.rediff.com
Result: "This site can't be reached" ✗
pfSense firewall blocked the connection
```

