## TP6 ADVANCED: Time-Based Rules (Schedules)

### Concept: Rules Active Only During Working Hours
Block HTTP only 9 AM - 5 PM, allow after hours

### Step 1: Create Schedule

**Why:** Control when rules apply

```
pfSense Dashboard:
Firewall → Schedules
Click "+ Add"
```

**Schedule Configuration:**
```
Schedule Name: WorkingHours
  (Letters and numbers only, no spaces)
Description: Normal Working Hours
```

**Select Month/Days:**
```
Month: June_21 (example)
Date: Click individual date (e.g., June 30)
  Or click day header (Mon, Tue, etc.) for recurring weekly
```

**Set Time Range:**
```
Start Time: 1:15 AM (example - adjust for real time)
Stop Time: 23:59 (nearly midnight)

Note: Cannot cross midnight (must be within same day)
Full day = 0:00 to 23:59
```

**Description:**
```
Time range description: Work day
```

**Save:**
```
Click "+ Add Time" → Click "Save"
```

**Result:** Schedule appears in Firewall/Schedules list

### Step 2: Create Rule with Schedule

**Why:** Apply rule only during specific times

```
Firewall → Rules → LAN
Click "Add"
```

**Configure Rule (same as before):**
```
Action: Reject
Interface: LAN
Protocol: TCP/UDP
Source: any
Destination: any
Port: HTTP (80)
Description: Rule for Rejecting any website using http (80) port during Working Hours
```

**Advanced Options:**
```
Scroll down → Click "Display Advanced"
```

**Select Schedule:**
```
Schedule: WorkingHours (dropdown)
Leave other options default
```

**Save:**
```
Click "Save" → Click "Apply Changes"
```

**Result:**
- 1:15 AM - 11:59 PM: HTTP blocked
- Outside this time: HTTP allowed

