## Why These Labs Matter (Real-World Context)

### TP4 - Host-Based Firewall
**Real-world:** Every corporate laptop has Windows Defender Firewall enabled
- Prevents malware from opening backdoors
- Blocks unauthorized remote access
- Example: Ransomware can't spread via SMB if RDP is blocked

### TP5 - Website Filtering
**Real-world:** Corporations block malware domains
- Block known phishing sites
- Prevent data exfiltration to attacker servers
- Example: Company blocks 10,000 malicious IPs using aliases

### TP6 - Port Blocking
**Real-world:** Force HTTPS adoption
- Block HTTP on public networks
- Ensure encrypted web traffic
- Example: Corporate firewall blocks port 80, allows only 443

