## Exam Questions This Covers

**Q: What's the difference between host-based and network firewalls?**
A: Host-based (TP4) protects individual machines, network-based (TP5/TP6) protects entire networks.

**Q: Why use aliases in pfSense?**
A: Group multiple IPs/domains so 1 rule replaces 100 rules.

**Q: What's the best action: Block or Reject?**
A: Reject = faster feedback to user; Block = stealthier (hides firewall).

**Q: How do time-based rules work?**
A: Rule only applies during specified hours (working hours example).

**Q: Why can't schedules cross midnight?**
A: Firewall processes rules within 24-hour day; split into 2 rules if crossing midnight needed.

